WHAT  — Microsoft's eighth-gen console shared the PS4's AMD blueprint but chose slower DDR3 main memory plus a small fast scratchpad of ESRAM — a more complex setup that started a step behind on graphics. A rocky media-focused launch was corrected over the generation.
